The Harren Charter was @@yours@@N. Filed during Midgaard's Founding
Generation, authorized by the First Stone Accord, sealed with the
city's sigil. A fortified manor tasked with processing the war dead.
The instrument remains in archive -- @@dparchment thirty-one, northern
estates drawer@@N. The Reckoning faction has requested its public
reading eleven times.

What Lord Harren built was orderly. Our ledgers show quarterly reports
through six generations: @@dbodies received, processed, bone stores
inventoried@@N. Then the reports stopped.

The @@rRoot Covenant@@N was a @@dcontainment failure@@N. A substrate theology
born among the estate's lowest laborers who rejected chapel bells in
favor of confession spoken into earth at root-contact points. Blood
opens listening channels. Roots carry memory farther than paper.
@@rBone remembers debt when ledgers fail.@@N This phrase appears in
Reckoning pamphlets with uncomfortable frequency.

Lord Harren invited the cult into his administrative structure with
no oversight audit. When he commissioned crystal cave exploration, no
risk assessment was filed. The @@rReversal Event@@N -- roots growing
toward ritual sites, the dead rising bark-skinned, the forest
replicating manor blueprints in biological material -- was
@@runaudited institutional transformation@@N.

Lord Harren was @@rretained@@N -- an estate revenant trapped inside the
system he helped create. The @@dThornwood Lich@@N emerged from the
substrate. Our Bureau classifies them as @@dfailed charter officers
operating beyond mandate@@N.

The @@rWild Hunt@@N has extended its patrol range farther toward the
@@yLantern Road@@N than in any prior generation. Hunt outriders
sighted within three miles of waystone fourteen. Threat to the Road
is threat to the city.

Current protocol: doubled patrols between waystones twelve and
eighteen, quarterly perimeter audits, standing advisory against solo
travel south of the canopy edge. The Bureau has petitioned for a
@@rcontainment expedition@@N four consecutive cycles. The Ledgerhouse
has approved none, citing @@dinsufficient precedent for charter
revocation of a self-sustaining necrotic estate@@N.

The Harren Charter was ours. Thornwood is what it became. The
Continuity faction calls this an anomaly. The Reckoning faction
calls it @@ra ledger entry that grew roots@@N.
